benchmark_config.jira_title: Implement/Test API: GET /1.0/kb/bundles/{bundleId}/auditLogsWithHistory - Retrieve bundle audit logs with history by id

covered: Valid Request: Scenarios cover successful retrieval (TC01) and various edge cases for valid bundles (TC02, TC08, TC18).
Empty Response: TC02 covers case of bundle with no audit logs (empty array).
Query Parameters: TC08 tests extra query parameters; multiple edge cases covered (TC11, TC19, TC20).
Authorization: Tests include missing token (TC05) and invalid token (TC06).
HTTP Method and Errors: Tests for wrong method (TC21) and various error responses (TC03 404, TC04 400, TC05/06 401, TC07 503, TC09 boundary, TC11 injection).
Performance/Scale: TC10 covers large audit log sets and performance assertion; TC17 covers concurrent requests.
State Variation: TC15 and TC16 cover database-empty and partially populated scenarios.
Integration/Consistency: TC14 checks consistency with other audit log endpoints.
gaps: Pagination: No explicit tests for paginating through large result sets (e.g., page size, page token, total count).
Caching Behavior: No tests verifying caching headers (ETag, Cache-Control) or client-side caching behavior.
Rate Limiting: No tests for rate limiting/throttling under bursty load.
Authorization - deeper coverage: No explicit 403 (Forbidden) scenario for authenticated users lacking permissions (only 401).
Internal Server Error: No explicit test simulating 500-level failures beyond service unavailable (503).
Edge cases around boundary UUIDs beyond those tested (e.g., all-zero vs. fully random boundary cases) could be expanded.
recommendations: Add explicit pagination tests to verify behavior with page size and page tokens, ensuring proper responses and metadata (total count, next/prev links).
Add tests validating caching headers (ETag, Last-Modified, Cache-Control) and conditional requests (If-None-Mord after GET).
Introduce rate-limiting tests (e.g., burst of requests) to confirm proper 429 or throttling behavior if applicable.
Add an explicit 403 Forbidden scenario to cover authenticated-but-unprivileged access.
Add tests simulating 500 Internal Server Error or database failure scenarios to verify robust error handling and proper messaging.
Expand edge-case UUID scenarios and ensure consistent behavior across boundary inputs.
